						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Colors $xE and $xF are preserved so that black can stay black, even when the greyscale bit is set.</div><br />Is this true? If so, the wiki is wrong:<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">wiki wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">When grayscale is turned on, the PPU ignores the lower nibble of each palette entry. This causes a bitwise AND with $30 on any value read from PPU $3F00-$3FFF, both on the display and through PPUDATA ($2007).</div><br /><br />I've always thought black turns into $00 (gray) as well when gr[a|e]yscale mode is turned on.</div>

					
